## üîç Nikto ‚Äì Web Server Vulnerability Scanner

**Nikto** is a web server scanner used to identify outdated software, dangerous files, misconfigurations, and known vulnerabilities.

Nikto performs thousands of checks against web servers and reports potential security issues.

```bash
# Basic web server scan
nikto -h https://www.example.com

# Scan a specific port
nikto -h https://www.example.com -p 8080

# Scan multiple hosts
nikto -h https://www.example1.com https://www.example2.com

# Save output to file
nikto -h https://www.example.com -o output.txt

# Suppress all output (useful for scripting)
nikto -h https://www.example.com -o /dev/null

# Full scan with tuning options
nikto -h https://www.example.com -maxtime 3600 -Tuning 8

# SSL certificate checks
nikto -h https://www.example.com -ssl

# Scan with authentication
nikto -h https://www.example.com -id admin:password

# Scan specific paths
nikto -h https://www.example.com -root /app,/secure

# Disable specific checks (e.g., XSS)
nikto -h https://www.example.com -C all,-XSS
